headlines.description: Angel Delgado had 18 points and 11 rebounds, his 57th career double-double, leading No. 15 Seton Hall to an 84-61 victory over Saint Peter's on Tuesday night in a rare game at the Pirates' old campus location Walsh Gym.
headlines.shortLinkText: Delgado keys No. 15 Seton Hall over Saint Peter's

video.headline: Seton Hall cruises against St. Peter's

headlines.description: Jacob Evans III had 24 points and eight rebounds as No. 25 Cincinnati recovered from back-to-back losses and handed Mississippi State its first defeat, 65-50 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 25 Cincinnati sends Mississippi State to 1st loss 65-50

headlines.description: Londell King had a season-high 17 points and seven rebounds, Jordan Walker added 14 points, and Morehead State beat NAIA Division II Kentucky Christian 85-57 on Tuesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morehead State beats NAIA DII Kentucky Christian 85-57

headlines.description: Donte Wright hit a corner 3-pointer with 4.2 seconds left in overtime and South Carolina State beat Charleston Southern 91-88 on Tuesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wright hits late 3, SC State tops Charleston Southern in OT

headlines.description: Jerome Robinson scored 21 points to lead Boston College to an 81-66 victory over Columbia on Tuesday in the Eagles' first game since knocking off then-No. 1 Duke.
headlines.shortLinkText: BC downs Columbia 81-66 behind Robinson's 21 points

headlines.description: Anthony Cowan scored 18 points, Kevin Huerter added 14 and Maryland overcame a sluggish start before pulling away from Division III Catholic 76-59 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maryland rolls past Catholic with 2nd half surge, 76-59

headlines.description: Deshawn Freeman had 14 points and 10 rebounds, Corey Sanders added 12 points and Rutgers beat Fordham 75-63 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Freeman has double-double; Rutgers beats Fordham 75-63

headlines.description: Tacko Fall scored 19 points and grabbed 11 rebounds, both season highs, and Central Florida won its third straight with a 61-53 win over Southeastern Louisiana Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCF wins 3rd straight,  knocking off SE Louisiana 61-53

headlines.description: Jordan Barnes totaled 22 points on 6-of-9 shooting from 3-point range and Indiana State dominated the second half and beat Green Bay 85-63 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes powers Indiana State to 85-63 win over Green Bay

headlines.description: Tookie Brown scored 17 points with four assists, Quan Jackson added a career-high 16 points off the bench, and Georgia Southern beat George Mason 74-51 on Tuesday night to open a six-game road trip with its third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia Southern downs George Mason 74-51

headlines.description: Alex King pumped in a season-high 24 points and Army rebounded from a 29-point drubbing at the hands of Wake Forest to post a 76-64 win over St. Francis Brooklyn Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alex King scored 24, leads Army past St. Francis (BKN) 76-64

headlines.description: Myles Stephens scored 19 points, Devin Cannady added 18 and Princeton used a 9-0 run late to beat Monmouth 69-58 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Princeton closes on 9-0 run to beat Monmouth 69-58

headlines.description: E.J. Crawford poured in 24 points and Deyshonee Much added 19 -- a career-high for Crawford and season best for Much -- and combined to hit seven of Iona's 11 3-pointers as the Gaels broke away from Yale 83-67 on Tuesday night, running their winning...
headlines.shortLinkText: Crawford, Much career nights spark Iona over Yale 83-67.

headlines.description: Justin Wright-Foreman scored 33 points, including seven in the final 1:38, and Hofstra rallied to beat Stony Brook 84-81 on Tuesday night to win its fourth straight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wright-Foreman scores 33, Hofstra beats Stony Brook 84-81

headlines.description: Jairus Lyles buried five 3-pointers and scored 27 and Arkel Lamar added 14 points and 13 rebounds to help Maryland-Baltimore County hold off winless Coppin State 81-74 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lyles, Lamar lead UMBC past winless Coppin State 81-74

headlines.description: Sean O'Brien scored 21 points to help Colgate snap a four-game losing streak heading into its 10-day break for exams, posting an 87-76 win over NJIT Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: O'Brien helps get Colgate back on track, beats NJIT, 87-76

headlines.description: Malik Maitland scored 21 points, Shawntrez Davis added 19 and Bethune-Cookman beat Cal Poly 67-53 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bethune-Cookman holds off Cal Poly, 67-53

headlines.description: JaKeenan Gant totaled 20 points, six rebounds, four steals and three blocked shots and Bryce Washington added a double-double to lead Louisiana to a 75-71 victory over Louisiana Tech on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gant, Washington help Louisiana topple Louisiana Tech 75-71

headlines.description: Isaiah Wright scored 20 points and Tyler Williams went 8 of 8 from the free throw line over the final 4:41 to help San Diego withstand a late charge in a 69-59 win over Colorado on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wright scores 20, San Diego upsets Colorado 69-59

headlines.description: Deng Geu and Rocky Kreuser combined to score 35 points as North Dakota State drubbed NAIA Valley City State, 101-58 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: North Dakota State stampedes past Valley City State, 101-58

headlines.description: Mike Daum scored 25 points with 10 rebounds and South Dakota State ran away from North Dakota 99-63 on Tuesday night to win their sixth straight at home.
headlines.shortLinkText: S Dakota St routs N Dakota 99-63 behind Daum's 25 points

headlines.description: Javon Bess tallied 20 points, six rebounds and five steals and Saint Louis took over to begin the second half and beat Murray State 69-55 on Tuesday night to snap the Racers' five-game win streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bess, Saint Louis halt Murray State's five-game win streak

headlines.description: Jordon Harris took and inbounds pass, drove the length of the floor and made the game-winning layup at the buzzer and Louisiana Monroe beat Grambling 59-57 on Tuesday night to end a two-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris' buzzer-beater lifts Louisiana Monroe over Grambling

headlines.description: Kamar McKnight shot five-for-nine from the floor in his first career start, Christian Mekowulu converted 12 of 16 free throws and each scored 14 points to lead Tennessee State past Alabama State 64-45 Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McKnight, Mekowulu left Tennessee St past Alabama St 64-45

headlines.description: Alcorn State trailed NAIA-member Fisk University at intermission and needed a strong second-half rally sparked by A.J. Mosby's 19-point effort to pull off a 77-69 win Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mosby leads late Alcorn State rally to beat NAIA Fisk, 77-69

headlines.description: Muhammad-Ali Abdur-Rahkman had 17 points and 10 rebounds, including a key 3-pointer, and Michigan beat Texas 59-52 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Abdur-Rahkman leads Michigan over Texas 59-52

video.headline: Texas' Sims puts Robinson on a poster

headlines.description: Kareem Brewton Jr. scored 19 points with three 3-pointers, Jeremiah Martin scored the go-ahead basket, and Memphis held off Albany 67-58 in Tuesday night's Gotham Classic matchup to win its third straight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Memphis holds off Albany for 67-58 win

headlines.description: Justin James scored on a fast-break after a steal, Hayden Dalton threw down back-to-back dunks and Nyaires Redding hit a pair of free throws with one second left and Wyoming slammed the door on Eastern Washington 93-88 in overtime Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dalton, James lead Wyoming past E Washington 93-88 in OT

headlines.description: Zach Lofton scored 29 points and New Mexico State won its second straight game over an in-state rival, handily beating Division II Eastern New Mexico, 84-62 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lofton leads New Mexico State past Eastern New Mexico, 84-62

headlines.description: Stephen Thompson Jr. scored 18 points with four 3-pointers and had five assists as Oregon State held on to beat Jacksonville State 70-69 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon State slips past Jacksonville State 70-69

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
